				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$E_{{{\mathrm{b}}}} = E_{{{{\mathrm{AB}}}}} - E_{{{\mathrm{A}}}}-E_{{{\mathrm{B}}}}$$\end{document}where EAB represents the total energy of the ions A and B, EA and EB represent the energy of A and B, respectively.
